getMarshaller

public JSourceMarshaller getMarshaller()
Returns the marshaller to rewrite the Java source represented by this.

This method can be called for every JSOM type and the returned marshaller will only rewrite those Java sources represented by the appropriate JSOM type.

removeTreeNode

protected static void removeTreeNode(AST2JSOMBase pNodeToRemove)
Removes the tree node that belongs to the stated AST2JSOMBase from it's parent tree node. Furthermore the appropriate tokens will be removed from the token stream.

Parameters:
pNodeToRemove - The owner of the tree node that should get removed.
Throws:
JSourceObjectizerInternalException - If the stated tree node is not a child of the stated parent node. I.e. it's up to the caller to ensure that the child exists. __TEST__

removeTreeNode

protected static void removeTreeNode(AST2JSOMBase pNodeToRemove,
                                     AST2JSOM.ChangeTokenBorder pLeftChangeTokenBorder,
                                     AST2JSOM.ChangeTokenBorder pRightChangeTokenBorder)
Removes the tree node that belongs to the stated AST2JSOMBase from it's parent tree node. Furthermore the appropriate tokens will be removed from the token stream.

Parameters:
pNodeToRemove - The owner of the tree node that should get removed.
pLeftChangeTokenBorder - See the comments for the enumeration declaration AST2JSOM.ChangeTokenBorder. If this argument is null removing will start with the left position of the stated node.
pRightChangeTokenBorder - See the comments for the enumeration declaration AST2JSOM.ChangeTokenBorder. If this argument is null removing will end at the right position of the stated node. __TEST__

removeTreeNode

protected static void removeTreeNode(AST2JSOMBase pNodeToRemove,
                                     AST2JSOMBase pFromNode,
                                     AST2JSOMBase pToNode)
Removes the tree node that belongs to the stated AST2JSOMBase from it's parent tree node. Furthermore the appropriate tokens will be removed from the token stream.

Parameters:
pNodeToRemove - The owner of the tree node that should get removed.
pFromNode - If not null all tokens from the right of this object up to the tokens that belong to pNodeToRemove will be removed, too.
pToNode - If not null all tokens from the left of this object up to the tokens that belong to pNodeToRemove will be removed, too. __TEST__
